19/06/2003
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- Slovenian President Janez Drnovsek pledged full support Wednesday (18 June) for Bulgaria's efforts to join the EU. 
He met with Bulgarian Prime Minister Simeon Saxe-Coburg and President Georgi Parvanov, focusing on bilateral co-operation and EU accession issues. 
Drnovsek met also with Parliament Chairman Ognyan Gerdzhikov and discussed opportunities for collaboration in the areas of science and culture, the social sector, transport, telecommunications, health care and tourism. 
(BNT, Nova TV, Television Slovenia, BTA - 18/06/03)
